title: Bunny Love
plot: The Warden requests the inmates wear bunny costumes as uniforms, but the Twins order some wolf costumes as well and make all Hell breaks lose when they start acting like the animals they are dressed as.

title: Superbar
plot: The Warden, opens as bar at SuperJail, in order to get a date with Alice. A group of prisoners plot an underwater escape!

title: Combaticus
plot: After the Warden finds an ancient coliseum underneath Superjail, he organizes a gladiatorial match for the inmates. The Twins create a fighter to fight the inmates.

title: Ladies Night
plot: The Warden makes a bet with his counterpart from a women's prison

title: Cold-Blooded
plot: The prison gets a new inmate, an Ed Gein-like serial killer, whose accidental death is credited to Jared, who is posing as a prisoner.

title: Don't Be a Negaton
plot: A well-known motivational speaker/cult leader comes to Superjail.

title: Terrorarium
plot: The Warden holds a science fair, but declares himself the winner, with his "Terrorarium" and makes several inmates go inside of it.

title: Mr. Grumpy Pants
plot: A little girl dying from cancer winds up at Superjail.

title: Dream Machine
plot: The Warden, paranoid after a dream, invents a device to monitor the prisoner's dreams to stop them from starting a riot.

title: Time Police: Part 1
plot: The Warden is arrested for crimes he will commit in the future.

title: Time Police: Part 2
plot: When the Warden is taken to another dimension by the Time Police, SuperJail is forced to closed.

title: Best Friends Forever
plot: Jailbot is shot down while escorting Jacknife to Superjail and the two of them must work together to survive terrible creatures. Back at Superjail, Jared and the prisoners are betting on their survival.

title: Mayhem Donor
plot: The Warden tries to make money by selling the prisoner's body parts.

title: Lord Stingray Crash Party
plot: An alien crash-lands and arrives at Superjail.

title: Hotchick
plot: An alien arrives at Superjail to hunt down the twins.

title: Gay Wedding
plot: Jean and Paul plan a wedding in Superjail.

title: Ghosts
plot: Superjail is haunted by ghosts.

title: Jailbot 2.0
plot: A new Jailbot model tries to take over Superjail.

title: The Budding of the Wurbuxx
plot: You'd have to be on drugs not to love The SuperJail Monthly Movie Matinee. Or at least that's what The Warden thinks, when the inmates don't love his Monthly Movie Matinee. Meanwhile, Alice is the only one who can help the Twins with a "feminine problem."

title: Superjail Grand Prix
plot: Superjail holds its annual Superjail Grand Prix. The winning team gets to go free, but we all know nothing comes free in Superjail.

title: Vacation
plot: The Warden takes the prisoners on a vacation.

title: Stingstress
plot: The Mistress returns to take over Superjail.

title: Superfail
plot: Jared, fed up with The Warden belittling him, pushes The Warden off a tall platform and he is injured, leaving Jared to run Superjail his way.

title: Uh-Oh Magic
plot: Warden takes up ventriloquism, but his little dummy steals the show.

title: Sticky Discharge
plot: Superjail is faced with its first parole... Ever!

title: Specialneeds
plot: The Warden makes Superjail handicap-accessible.

title: The Trouble with Triples
plot: The Warden makes a virtual reality video game for the prisoners.

title: Nightshift
plot: Alice discovers a hidden talent for cooking and sets out to find the perfect truffle.

title: Oedipusmess
plot: When an inmate becomes a daddy, Superjail's population explodes.

title: Planet Radio
plot: When a pirate radio station hits Superail, the Warden fights back with some programming of his own.

title: Burn Stoolie Burn
plot: An inmate teaches the Warden about friendship and fire.

title: Superhell!
plot: Superjail becomes hell on earth-more than it usually is, at least.

title: The Last Pack
plot: The Warden bans smoking, which begins a deadly race for the last pack.

title: Jean & Paul & Beefy & Alice
plot: A romantic spa outing causes an outbreak that's way nastier than foot fungus.

title: The Superjail Inquisitor
plot: The Warden's belief in a fairy tale monster pushes him to fanatical lengths.

title: Superstorm!
plot: A weather-controlling robot causes some deadly climate change.

title: The Superjail Six
plot: Superjail's darkest secret leads to backwater neighbors who throw a killer hoedown.
